{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"cling wrap, rolling pin, pasta machine, large saucepot (approx. 4-5 qt.), stove","id":"r330879","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-V2Er_DDEBtI\/XZM0TPkHsLI\/AAAAAAAAa68\/TM_sjcaSdMkbV7sz0lKfa0jjtTgDVSrdQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_v6CO-7TFGZSmv6gM.png","title":"Homemade Pasta","publishedAt":"2018-06-22T00:00:00Z","ingredients2":[{"content":"7 oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust"},{"content":"2 large eggs"},{"content":"1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil"},{"content":"salt, to boil with pasta"},{"content":"water, to boil pasta"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"8 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"38 g","calories":"1029 kJ \/ 246 kcal"},"preparations2":[{"content":"Place flour, eggs and oil into mixing bowl and knead <b>2 min\/<b>, until a crumbled dough forms. Work the dough with your hands and form a ball, wrap in cling wrap, let rest for 15 minutes."},{"content":"Transfer dough to a well-floured work surface and divide into four parts. Roll each piece of dough with a rolling pin into an elongated shape and feed through the pasta machine while guiding the dough. Run dough through pasta machine with rollers set on most open setting; fold dough into thirds and roll it back through the pasta maker. If dough sticks, coat with a little more flour. Fold and roll the dough three more times on this setting. Adjust rollers to the next level of thinness and guide dough back through the machine with the back of your hand, repeating the process until dough is approximately 1\/16 inch thick. Keep remaining dough covered to prevent from drying out. Repeat with remaining dough. Cut pasta into desired shapes (see Variation)."},{"content":"Cook pasta on stove top with plenty of boiling and salted water (approx. 1 tbsp salt per 16 cups water) for 2-4 minutes depending on shape and thickness of dough. Drain pasta and serve warm, seasoned with sauce to taste."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For better results, leave the cut dough to dry 1-2 hours on a floured cloth.","To increase the quantity of pasta, add 1 egg for every 3.5 oz flour. Mix a maximum of 17.5 oz flour and 5 eggs one at a time and increase kneading time to 3 minutes.","Replace all-purpose flour with 00 extra fine unbleached flour for a more supple and malleable dough that is easy to work with.","For green pasta: follow the basic recipe by adding 3.5 oz flour and 2.5 oz fresh spinach leaves, washed and dried or defrosted and well drained. Place flour and spinach into mixing bowl and blend <strong>20 sec\/speed 9<\/strong>. Add eggs and oil and knead <strong>2 min\/<\/strong>.","For egg-free pasta: replace the two eggs with 4 oz tomato sauce and proceed as indicated in the recipe.","For basil pasta: place 0.5 oz fresh basil leaves and flour into mixing bowl and blend <strong>20 sec\/speed 9<\/strong>. Add 1 tbsp water, 2 eggs and 1 tbsp oil and knead <strong>2 min\/<\/strong>.","Cut dough into desired shapes according to the type of pasta you want to prepare. Lasagna or ravioli: cut dough into rectangles (8 in. x 4 in.). Tagliatelle: cut into strips (approx. 1\/16 in. x 12 in.). Bow ties: cut small rectangles (1 in. x 2 in.) and pinch the center of each rectangle to form a bow tie."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","1h","4 portions"]}